#Install Direction
# 1. Change the "INSTALL.sh" script permissons using chmod +x
# 2. Edit "liinfo" for your server role
# 3. Run "INSTALL.sh"
# 4. Run "sys.info.sh" that appears on the desktop
# 5. edit "liinfo" in /root/bin/backup to alter the appearence of the zenity box
# 6. edit "sys.info.sh" for window size and timeout
#
#
#
#What Scripts do
#liinfo
# - Runs multiple commands to grab all info wanted and then puts it into the file 'sys.info'
#sys.info.sh
# - Runs the 'liinfo' script to make sure it is updated, then runs a zenity script to show the contents of 'sys.info'
#
#If you get a Gtk warning then run "$DISPLAY" in terminal, then it should give a number like '1.0' take that number and 
#instert it into 'sys.info.sh' "--display= "
#
#
#
#To display image on background
#download ImageMagick-devel
#Install ImageMagick
#run convert in your folder with sys.info and the images you want to use as your background


